 over the problem of workplace accidents, they transformed the older practice of commercial insurance into an instrument of state intervention, thereby creating an entirely new conception of law, the state, and social solidarity. What emerged was a new system of social insurance guaranteed by the state. The Birth of Solidarity is a classic work of social and political theory that will appeal to all those interested in labor power, the making and dismantling of the welfare state, and Foucauldian notions of governmentality, security, risk, and the limits of liberalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAccident insurancezFrancexHistory. 0aSocial legislationzFrancexHistory. 0aSocial securityzFrancexHistory. 0aWelfare statexHistory. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh1 aCooper, Melinda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Melinda, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnson, Timothy Scott.1 aScott Johnson, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478009214zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478009214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478009214/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  D